title: Jigokuraku
summary: The Tokugawa Dynasty. One of the most skillful ninja and notorious assassin is captured, but he has a chance to avoid execution. To do so, he must travel to a mysterious island shrouded in legend and find the elixir of immortality.

title: My Happy Marriage
summary: Misery seems everlasting in Miyo Saimoris life. Born from an arranged marriage, she was quickly discarded after her mothers tragic death. Her father remarried, and her younger half-sister Kaya received all the affection, while Miyo was degraded to a lowly servant. Lacking the strength to fight against her familys abuse, Miyo loses hope that her luck will ever turn. Unexpectedly, Miyos father summons her to deliver surprising news: she is to marry Kiyoka Kudou, the head of the distinguished Kudou family. Despite his noble background, Kiyoka is known to be a callous man who has thus far dismissed all of his former fiancées. Upon arriving at the Kudou household, Miyo expects coarse treatment and to be tossed aside. However, contrary to her assumptions, Kiyoka shows her the kindness and love that she has desperately needed. Marrying Kiyoka may be Miyos one chance to break free from her neglectful family and embrace a life of happiness.

title: Solo Leveling
summary: Humanity was caught at a precipice a decade ago when the first gates—portals linked with other dimensions that harbor monsters immune to conventional weaponry—emerged around the world. Alongside the appearance of the gates, various humans were transformed into hunters and bestowed superhuman abilities. Responsible for entering the gates and clearing the dungeons within, many hunters chose to form guilds to secure their livelihoods.Sung Jin-Woo is an E-rank hunter dubbed as the weakest hunter of all mankind. While exploring a supposedly safe dungeon, he and his party encounter an unusual tunnel leading to a deeper area. Enticed by the prospect of treasure, the group presses forward, only to be confronted with horrors beyond their imagination. Miraculously, Jin-Woo survives the incident and soon finds that he now has access to an interface visible only to him. This mysterious system promises him the power he has long dreamed of—but everything comes at a price.

title: Classroom of the Elite
summary: On the surface, Koudo Ikusei Senior High School is a utopia. The students enjoy an unparalleled amount of freedom, and it is ranked highly in Japan. However, the reality is less than ideal. Four classes, A through D, are ranked in order of merit, and only the top classes receive favorable treatment. Kiyotaka Ayanokouji is a student of Class D, where the school dumps its worst. There he meets the unsociable Suzune Horikita, who believes she was placed in Class D by mistake and desires to climb all the way to Class A, and the seemingly amicable class idol Kikyou Kushida, whose aim is to make as many friends as possible. While class membership is permanent, class rankings are not; students in lower ranked classes can rise in rankings if they score better than those in the top ones. Additionally, in Class D, there are no bars on what methods can be used to get ahead. In this cutthroat school, can they prevail against the odds and reach the top?

title: The Eminence in Shadow
summary: What did you want to be when you were a kid? A famous soccer player? A superhero? Or maybe a singer, gathering huge crowds at concerts? All this is not about our protagonist Sid, because he has always admired people from behind the scenes, those who almost do not take any action in the open, but appear only at the most crucial moment and, having done the job, disappears without a trace. In our world, it is difficult to pull off such a thing, because no matter what you do, you can't go against the atomic bomb. And so, thinking about ways to repel nuclear weapons with his bare hands, our hero comes to the conclusion that there is no way without magic. Conveniently it turned out, because soon after that the guy met the notorious truck, which sent him to the other world, or to be more precise, to the world full of swords, magic and other delights of fantasy universes. Now Sid will have no obstacles on his way to becoming the greatest ruler from the shadows. Translated with DeepL.com (free version)

title: Chainsaw Man
summary: Denji has to completely change his life to pay off his father's exorbitant debts. He becomes the Yakuza's handmaiden in the difficult business of destroying demons. Not only sleep and rest, but also communication with his beloved girl. Only the devil's pet-assistant Pochita brings a little variety in the succession of bloody everyday life. Now Denji has only one goal - money, only in them he sees a chance for release. Wanting to get a quick profit, the guy forgets about caution and dies in one of the fights. The faithful Pochito saves his master by merging with him and giving him the ability to partially transform into a chainsaw. Translated with DeepL.com (free version)

title: Sword Art Online
summary:
The beginning of the twenty-first century, the Japanese genius created a universe, the release of which was awaited by the entire world of "sword art". Gamers got the opportunity of complete immersion. The novelty became the most expected and ten thousand samples with lightning speed disappeared from the shelves. Everyone entered reality, dissolved into it and gathered in the City. The creator appeared. A huge black shadow explained to the participants that it was possible to return to the real world only by going through the whole game. But there is one cruel moment, virtual death means death in real life and it is impossible to pass it at random. After the loud words the creator vaporized, leaving the players alone.

The reaction to the message was different. Desperation set in, some teamed up with others, and some, like Kazuto's character, went it alone. Kirigaya is an orphan and so once in this world, he loses nothing. He is a beta tester and knowing everything about the game, he quickly gained popularity with the players. The hero realizes that without interaction with others he can not get out and has to establish contacts with other players. And while the swordfight is going on, everyone will see a lot of amazing things.

title: Sword Art Online 2
summary:
Game worlds are still spreading, and a world tree is growing in Alfheim. every conceivable villain has gotten what they deserve. Kayaba, the dark genius, will pay in full. Asuna has been freed and returned home, and the evil Sugo has gotten what's coming to him.
The man, seeking to escape from the constant oppression of circumstances beyond the boundaries of the fictional world, constantly expands it, so that there would be enough space for all those seeking refuge. And in the process, he unlocks the power of his brain. If this expansion can't be stopped, it must be led. That's what Kirito told Asuna, his lover. Naturally, without knowing the first thing, she agreed.

title: Ningen Fushin no Boukensha-tachi ga Sekai wo Sukuu you desu
family: Ningen Fushin no Boukensha-tachi ga Sekai wo Sukuu you desu
summary:
It's a fool's errand to expect justice from life. Nick, an experienced adventurer, was personally convinced of this when he discovered that his friendly guild turned out to be a snake's nest. The guy noticed the embezzlement of the guild's budget, brought out the thief, but in response received only general condemnation and accusations of trying to shift his responsibility to an innocent man. Nick leaves the group and pours his grief in bars.
Alcoholic madness stops after another feast. The four drinking buddies turned out to be the same guild-loyal adventurers. Having sobered up a little, the fighters decide to unite. The new group is strong, and the fighters are loyal to each other. They are up to the toughest tasks. As the authority of the team grows, so do the tasks. One day they are asked to save humanity. But does a collection of scum and traitors deserve to be saved? Each member of the group tries to find the answer on their own. Only Nick is sure that good deeds are the key to a successful reboot of both his life and his new comrades. He sincerely tries to help everyone and gradually becomes the leader of the world's best group of adventurers.

title: Kyokou Suiri
summary:
When Iwanaga Kotoko was eleven years old, she was kidnapped by demons who intended to make her their "Goddess of Wisdom" - an intermediary between the human and spiritual worlds. It was unexpected, but the girl quickly agreed to the adventure. Alas, there was a price to pay for power, and she lost her right eye and left leg. Since that day, she has become an important person in the spirit world and is now and again approached by the ekai and mythical creatures for advice.
Six years have passed since then. Twenty-two-year-old student Kuro Sakuragawa has just gone through a painful breakup with the girl he loves. She had dumped him because the guy ran away when she met a kappa. Kuro, on the other hand, really liked Kotoko, and she decided to marry him by all means. But how to win his heart? He becomes her partner in solving supernatural conflicts. He becomes her partner in solving supernatural conflicts, and as it turns out, he also has some superpowers, and Kuro is quite good at what he does.

title: Darwins Game
summary:
A seventeen-year-old boy named Sudo Kaname gets involved in a tantalizing adventure that a friend of his got him into. The friend suggested that he play a mobile game called "Darwin's Game" because he couldn't play it alone. And the guy without doubt installed the application on the link received from his friend. The essence of gameplay is the destruction of opponents... it would seem - an ordinary survival toy, except that it is not about the virtual universe.
Players have to fight each other in the real world, and losing in it means one thing - death. And Sudo is now forced to suppress his morals to defeat all opponents... because only winning will help to leave "Darwin's Game". Each gamer receives a special ability called "sigil" that helps in battles. In addition, for each victory, players earn points that can be exchanged for real money. This means that the stakes are raised significantly...

All this is not about our protagonist Sid, because he has always admired people from behind the scenes, those who almost do not take any action in the open, but appear only at the most crucial moment and, having done the job, disappears without a trace. In our world, it is difficult to pull off such a thing, because no matter what you do, you can't go against the atomic bomb. And so, thinking about ways to repel nuclear weapons with his bare hands, our hero comes to the conclusion that there is no way without magic. Conveniently it turned out, because soon after that the guy met the notorious truck, which sent him to the other world, or to be more precise, to the world full of swords, magic and other delights of fantasy universes. Now Sid will have no obstacles on his way to becoming the greatest ruler from the shadows. Translated with DeepL.com (free version)

title: Chainsaw Man
summary: Denji has to completely change his life to pay off his father's exorbitant debts. He becomes the Yakuza's handmaiden in the difficult business of destroying demons. Not only sleep and rest, but also communication with his beloved girl. Only the devil's pet-assistant Pochita brings a little variety in the succession of bloody everyday life. Now Denji has only one goal - money, only in them he sees a chance for release. Wanting to get a quick profit, the guy forgets about caution and dies in one of the fights. The faithful Pochito saves his master by merging with him and giving him the ability to partially transform into a chainsaw. Translated with DeepL.com (free version)

title: Sword Art Online
summary:
The beginning of the twenty-first century, the Japanese genius created a universe, the release of which was awaited by the entire world of "sword art". Gamers got the opportunity of complete immersion. The novelty became the most expected and ten thousand samples with lightning speed disappeared from the shelves. Everyone entered reality, dissolved into it and gathered in the City. The creator appeared. A huge black shadow explained to the participants that it was possible to return to the real world only by going through the whole game. But there is one cruel moment, virtual death means death in real life and it is impossible to pass it at random. After the loud words the creator vaporized, leaving the players alone.

The reaction to the message was different. Desperation set in, some teamed up with others, and some, like Kazuto's character, went it alone. Kirigaya is an orphan and so once in this world, he loses nothing. He is a beta tester and knowing everything about the game, he quickly gained popularity with the players. The hero realizes that without interaction with others he can not get out and has to establish contacts with other players. And while the swordfight is going on, everyone will see a lot of amazing things.

title: Sword Art Online 2
summary:
Game worlds are still spreading, and a world tree is growing in Alfheim. every conceivable villain has gotten what they deserve. Kayaba, the dark genius, will pay in full. Asuna has been freed and returned home, and the evil Sugo has gotten what's coming to him.
The man, seeking to escape from the constant oppression of circumstances beyond the boundaries of the fictional world, constantly expands it, so that there would be enough space for all those seeking refuge. And in the process, he unlocks the power of his brain. If this expansion can't be stopped, it must be led. That's what Kirito told Asuna, his lover. Naturally, without knowing the first thing, she agreed.

title: Ningen Fushin no Boukensha-tachi ga Sekai wo Sukuu you desu
family: Ningen Fushin no Boukensha-tachi ga Sekai wo Sukuu you desu
summary:
It's a fool's errand to expect justice from life. Nick, an experienced adventurer, was personally convinced of this when he discovered that his friendly guild turned out to be a snake's nest. The guy noticed the embezzlement of the guild's budget, brought out the thief, but in response received only general condemnation and accusations of trying to shift his responsibility to an innocent man. Nick leaves the group and pours his grief in bars.
Alcoholic madness stops after another feast. The four drinking buddies turned out to be the same guild-loyal adventurers. Having sobered up a little, the fighters decide to unite. The new group is strong, and the fighters are loyal to each other. They are up to the toughest tasks. As the authority of the team grows, so do the tasks. One day they are asked to save humanity. But does a collection of scum and traitors deserve to be saved? Each member of the group tries to find the answer on their own. Only Nick is sure that good deeds are the key to a successful reboot of both his life and his new comrades. He sincerely tries to help everyone and gradually becomes the leader of the world's best group of adventurers.

title: Kyokou Suiri
summary:
When Iwanaga Kotoko was eleven years old, she was kidnapped by demons who intended to make her their "Goddess of Wisdom" - an intermediary between the human and spiritual worlds. It was unexpected, but the girl quickly agreed to the adventure. Alas, there was a price to pay for power, and she lost her right eye and left leg. Since that day, she has become an important person in the spirit world and is now and again approached by the ekai and mythical creatures for advice.
Six years have passed since then. Twenty-two-year-old student Kuro Sakuragawa has just gone through a painful breakup with the girl he loves. She had dumped him because the guy ran away when she met a kappa. Kuro, on the other hand, really liked Kotoko, and she decided to marry him by all means. But how to win his heart? He becomes her partner in solving supernatural conflicts. He becomes her partner in solving supernatural conflicts, and as it turns out, he also has some superpowers, and Kuro is quite good at what he does.

title: Darwins Game
summary:
A seventeen-year-old boy named Sudo Kaname gets involved in a tantalizing adventure that a friend of his got him into. The friend suggested that he play a mobile game called "Darwin's Game" because he couldn't play it alone. And the guy without doubt installed the application on the link received from his friend. The essence of gameplay is the destruction of opponents... it would seem - an ordinary survival toy, except that it is not about the virtual universe.
Players have to fight each other in the real world, and losing in it means one thing - death. And Sudo is now forced to suppress his morals to defeat all opponents... because only winning will help to leave "Darwin's Game". Each gamer receives a special ability called "sigil" that helps in battles. In addition, for each victory, players earn points that can be exchanged for real money. This means that the stakes are raised significantly...

title: Jigokuraku
summary: The Tokugawa Dynasty. One of the most skillful ninja and notorious assassin is captured, but he has a chance to avoid execution. To do so, he must travel to a mysterious island shrouded in legend and find the elixir of immortality.

title: My Happy Marriage
summary: Misery seems everlasting in Miyo Saimoris life. Born from an arranged marriage, she was quickly discarded after her mothers tragic death. Her father remarried, and her younger half-sister Kaya received all the affection, while Miyo was degraded to a lowly servant. Lacking the strength to fight against her familys abuse, Miyo loses hope that her luck will ever turn. Unexpectedly, Miyos father summons her to deliver surprising news: she is to marry Kiyoka Kudou, the head of the distinguished Kudou family. Despite his noble background, Kiyoka is known to be a callous man who has thus far dismissed all of his former fiancées. Upon arriving at the Kudou household, Miyo expects coarse treatment and to be tossed aside. However, contrary to her assumptions, Kiyoka shows her the kindness and love that she has desperately needed. Marrying Kiyoka may be Miyos one chance to break free from her neglectful family and embrace a life of happiness.

title: Solo Leveling
summary: Humanity was caught at a precipice a decade ago when the first gates—portals linked with other dimensions that harbor monsters immune to conventional weaponry—emerged around the world. Alongside the appearance of the gates, various humans were transformed into hunters and bestowed superhuman abilities. Responsible for entering the gates and clearing the dungeons within, many hunters chose to form guilds to secure their livelihoods.Sung Jin-Woo is an E-rank hunter dubbed as the weakest hunter of all mankind. While exploring a supposedly safe dungeon, he and his party encounter an unusual tunnel leading to a deeper area. Enticed by the prospect of treasure, the group presses forward, only to be confronted with horrors beyond their imagination. Miraculously, Jin-Woo survives the incident and soon finds that he now has access to an interface visible only to him. This mysterious system promises him the power he has long dreamed of—but everything comes at a price.

title: Classroom of the Elite
summary: On the surface, Koudo Ikusei Senior High School is a utopia. The students enjoy an unparalleled amount of freedom, and it is ranked highly in Japan. However, the reality is less than ideal. Four classes, A through D, are ranked in order of merit, and only the top classes receive favorable treatment. Kiyotaka Ayanokouji is a student of Class D, where the school dumps its worst. There he meets the unsociable Suzune Horikita, who believes she was placed in Class D by mistake and desires to climb all the way to Class A, and the seemingly amicable class idol Kikyou Kushida, whose aim is to make as many friends as possible. While class membership is permanent, class rankings are not; students in lower ranked classes can rise in rankings if they score better than those in the top ones. Additionally, in Class D, there are no bars on what methods can be used to get ahead. In this cutthroat school, can they prevail against the odds and reach the top?
